1	{"candidate_kind": "source_target", "source_slug": "malentine-velaryon", "source_bucket": "characters-house-velaryon", "source_section": "## Origins", "target_slug": "alyn-velaryon", "target_page": "Alyn_Velaryon", "anchor_text": "Alyn of Hull", "snippet": "...ded as [Lord of the Tides](wiki:Lord_of_the_Tides) by his bastard grandson, «Alyn of Hull» . This succession was not uncontested. Malentine and his only surviving bro...", "backlink_count": 156, "target_type": "character.human", "evidence_paragraph": "When Lord Corlys died in «132 AC», he was succeeded as «Lord of the Tides» by his bastard grandson, «Alyn of Hull». This succession was not uncontested. Malentine and his only surviving brother, Ser «Rhogar», yet again took their own claim to the «small council» in «King’s Landing». When the «Hand of the King» and the «regents» ruled against them, Malentine and Rhogar refused to accept the decision. As «Mushroom» put it in «his testimony», *\"lacking tongues with which to make their appeal, they preferred to argue with swords\"*. The plot of the silent brothers to assassinate Alyn failed when the guards at «Castle Driftmark» proved loyal to the Sea Snake's memory and his chosen heir. Ser Malentine was slain during the attempt, his brother Rhogar captured and later sent to the «Night's Watch».", "staging_verbs_present": [], "valid_edge_types": ["ADVISES", "AFFLICTED_BY", "ALIAS_OF", "ALLIES_WITH", "ANCESTOR_OF", "APPEARS_TO_FULFILL", "APPOINTS", "ASSAULTS", "ATTACKS", "BANISHES", "BESIEGES", "BESTOWS_KNIGHTHOOD_ON", "BETRAYS", "BETROTHED_TO", "BONDED_TO", "BREAKS_VOW", "BUILT", "CADET_BRANCH_OF", "CAPTAIN_OF", "CAPTURES", "CAUSES", "CITED_BY", "CLAIMS", "COMMANDS", "COMMANDS_IN", "COMPANION_OF", "CONSPIRES_WITH", "CONTEMPORARY_WITH", "CONTRACTED_WITH", "CONTRADICTS", "CONTRASTS", "COURTS", "COUSIN_OF", "CREW_OF", "CROWNS_QUEEN_OF_LOVE_AND_BEAUTY", "CURSES", "DECEIVED_BY", "DECEIVES", "DEFEATS", "DEPICTED_IN", "DEPOSES", "DIED_OF", "DISGUISED_AS", "DISTRUSTS", "D