{"source_slug":"marilda-of-hull","target_slug":"130-ac","target_type":"character.human","evidence_paragraph":"After her father's death a decade later, Marilda sold his shipyard and used the proceeds to captain a trading cog she called *«Mouse»)*. By «130 AC» Marilda owned seven ships, which her sons served on."}
{"source_slug":"marilda-of-hull","target_slug":"addam-velaryon","target_type":"character.human","evidence_paragraph":"Marilda was the daughter of a shipwright at «Hull». She was frequently seen at the shipyards, often underfoot. Marilda was sixteen years old when she gave birth to «Addam» in «114 AC», and she was barely eighteen when «Alyn» was birthed in «115 AC». She refused to name the father of her sons."}
{"source_slug":"marilda-of-hull","target_slug":"aegon-ii-targaryen","target_type":"character.human","evidence_paragraph":"After the death of Rhaenyra in the «fall of Dragonstone» and the pardoning of Corlys by Queen «Alicent Hightower», Alyn agreed to transport King «Aegon II Targaryen» from Dragonstone back to «King's Landing». Protected by a dozen Velaryon galleys, Marilda sailed the king to the capital aboard *Mouse*."}
{"source_slug":"marilda-of-hull","target_slug":"alicent-hightower","target_type":"character.human","evidence_paragraph":"After the death of Rhaenyra in the «fall of Dragonstone» and the pardoning of Corlys by Queen «Alicent Hightower», Alyn agreed to transport King «Aegon II Targaryen» from Dragonstone back to «King's Landing». Protected by a dozen Velaryon galleys, Marilda sailed the king to the capital aboard *Mouse*."}
{"source_slug":"marilda-of-hull","target_slug":"bastard","target_type":"title","evidence_paragraph":"When Prince «Jacaerys Velaryon» called for «dragonseeds» during the «Dance of the Dragons», Marilda claimed that her children, who had silver hair and «purple eyes», had been fathered by Ser «Laenor Velaryon», who had died in «120 AC». Grand Maester «Munkun» and Septon «Eustace») agree with Marilda's claim, but «Mushroom» wrote that Addam and Alyn had actually been fathered by Laenor's own sire, Lord «Corlys Velaryon», a frequent visitor to Driftmark's shipyards. After Addam became a «dragonrider» on «Seasmoke», who was Laenor's own mount, Corlys and Jacaerys convinced Queen «Rhaenyra Targaryen» to legitimize the «bastard» brothers as Velaryons. Addam eventually died in the «Second Battle of Tumbleton»."}
{"source_slug":"marilda-of-hull","target_slug":"bold-marilda","target_type":"object.artifact","evidence_paragraph":"When Alyn Oakenfist led a fleet of merchantmen to «Dorne» and the «Free Cities» in «136 AC», the «Lord of the Tides» commanded from a galley named *«Bold Marilda»*."}
